   311	  `store.list_proposals(state="ready")` returning empty), mid-flow
   312	  `submit` failure surfaces orphaned proposal IDs to the user.
   313	  Driven by `httpx.AsyncClient` against the real ASGI app so
   314	  cookie/session round-tripping is authentic.
   315	- `tests/test_security_invariants.py` — focused unit tests that
   316	  pin the security guarantees codex flagged:
   317	  - The shared bearer never appears in any rendered HTML, any
   318	    JSON-line log captured during a test request, or any
   319	    `Set-Cookie` header.
   320	  - Cookie attributes: `HttpOnly=True`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Path=/`.
   321	    `Secure` is `True` iff `--secure-cookies` is on.
   322	  - CSRF token is per-session and rotates only on session-secret
   323	    rotation; same-token reuse across requests is allowed.
   324	- `tests/test_partial_write_recovery.py` — focused tests that pin
   325	  the planner-flow state-machine guarantees:
   326	  - Forced `mark_proposal_ready` failure (via monkeypatched
   327	    store) leaves all earlier proposals in `drafting`, none in
   328	    `ready`. Asserts the orchestrator's
   329	    `_dispatch_implement_tasks` would not pick them up.
   330	  - Forced `submit` failure surfaces orphaned `ready`
   331	    proposal IDs in the rendered error page.
   332	- `tests/test_e2e_real_subprocess.py` — `pytest.mark.e2e` test that
   333	  reuses the Phase 8b subprocess scaffold (spawn task-store-server +
   334	  UI service on ephemeral ports) and drives one plan task to
   335	  submission via the UI's HTTP surface, then asserts the resulting
   336	  task-store state via a separate `StoreClient`. This is the only
   337	  test that exercises the UI service against a real
   338	  task-store-server subprocess.
   339	
   340	### B. Auth model (UI scope only — does not change wire protocol)
   341	
   342	- The UI service is started with `--shared-token <T>` and passes
   343	  `T` as the bearer to its `StoreClient`.
   344	- The browser receives an `itsdangerous`-signed session cookie
   345	  holding `{"worker_id": "<--worker-id>", "csrf": "<random hex>"}`
   346	  once the user "signs in". The sign-in for Phase 9 is a
   347	  no-questions form ("Continue as <worker-id>"); real auth is
   348	  Milestone 3. The cookie carries the worker_id so subsequent
   349	  claim/submit requests know who the human is, and a per-session
   350	  CSRF token used by mutating routes.
   351	- **Cookie attributes** are pinned: `HttpOnly=True`, `SameSite=Lax`,
   352	  `Secure=False` (toggleable via `--secure-cookies` for deployments
   353	  behind TLS — defaults off so localhost dev doesn't break).
   354	  `Path=/`, no `Domain`. Cookie max-age tracks the session-secret
   355	  rotation: any restart with a fresh `--session-secret`
   356	  invalidates outstanding sessions.
   357	- **CSRF protection** for every mutating route (POST /planner/...).
   358	  A hidden `_csrf` form input carries the per-session token; the
   359	  server compares against the cookie's `csrf` field via constant-
   360	  time compare and rejects mismatches with 400. `SameSite=Lax`
   361	  alone is **not** treated as sufficient — explicit token check
   362	  is added because reference UIs in the wild often get cross-site
   363	  POST'd through HTML form action attributes.
   364	- **Bearer-token hygiene.** The `--shared-token` value never reaches
   365	  the browser, the rendered HTML, the server logs, or the test
   366	  fixture log files. Specifically:
   367	  - The session cookie does not contain it.
   368	  - JSON-line logs (via `eden_service_common.logging`) elide
   369	    `Authorization` headers.
   370	  - The bearer-leak test (see §F) asserts no log line, no rendered
   371	    response body, and no `Set-Cookie` value contains the token's
   372	    string.
   373	- **Session cookie does not bypass the wire boundary.** A leaked
   374	  cookie can act on behalf of the worker_id it names (claim, submit
   375	  through the UI) but cannot bypass the UI service to talk to the
   376	  task-store directly — the shared bearer is held only in the UI
   377	  process. Until Milestone-3 auth, "compromise of the cookie ==
   378	  compromise of that worker_id's UI actions" is the documented
   379	  threat model.
   380	
   381	### C. Planner request flow (the spec-to-code map)
   382	
   383	For each planner action, the corresponding `Store` (i.e.
   384	`StoreClient`) calls are pinned here so the codex review can check
   385	the implementation against this spec rather than rederiving it from
   386	the templates.
   387	
   388	The planner module is informed by the `experiment_config` loaded at
   389	start-up. The planner page surfaces:
   390	
   391	- The experiment's `objective` (read-only banner).
   392	- The experiment's `metrics_schema` (read-only side panel showing
   393	  metric names and types). The planner contract per
   394	  `spec/v0/03-roles.md` §2 explicitly grants the planner read
   395	  access to `metrics_schema` and `objective`; surfacing both is
   396	  required to satisfy that contract.
   397	- A "context" panel listing the most recent proposals
   398	  (`store.list_proposals(state=None)` capped at the 20 most
   399	  recent) and trials (`store.list_trials(status=None)` capped at
   400	  the 20 most recent). This satisfies the implicit "what has
   401	  already been tried" read access the planner needs to draft
   402	  meaningfully.
   403	
   404	The proposal form itself collects per-proposal slug, priority,
   405	parent-commits, and rationale-markdown.
   406	
   407	1. **List pending plan tasks** (`GET /planner`):
   408	   - `store.list_tasks(kind="plan", state="pending")` — render rows.
   409	2. **Claim** (`POST /planner/{task_id}/claim`):
   410	   - CSRF check.
   411	   - `claim = store.claim(task_id, worker_id=session.worker_id,
   412	     expires_at=now() + timedelta(seconds=claim_ttl_seconds))`.
   413	   - Save `claim.token` in the session keyed by `task_id`.
   414	   - Render `planner_claim.html` with an empty proposal-row plus
   415	     "add another" / "submit (success)" / "submit (error)" buttons.
   416	3. **Submit success** (`POST /planner/{task_id}/submit`):
   417	   - CSRF check.
   418	   - Parse and **fully validate** N proposal rows from the form
   419	     before any store mutation. Validation includes: slug
   420	     pattern, priority float-parse, parent_commits non-empty,
   421	     rationale-markdown non-empty.
   422	   - **Phase 1 of the write — proposals as `drafting`.** For each
   423	     proposal: write its rationale markdown to
   424	     `<artifacts-dir>/<proposal_id>.md`, build a `file://` URI,
   425	     then `store.create_proposal(Proposal(state="drafting", ...))`.
   426	     A `drafting` proposal is invisible to the orchestrator's
   427	     `list_proposals(state="ready")` dispatch path, so a
   428	     mid-loop failure here orphans only `drafting` proposals,
   429	     which are safe to ignore (no implement task is dispatched).
   430	   - **Phase 2 of the write — flip to `ready`.** Once every
   431	     `create_proposal` has returned, loop again and call
   432	     `store.mark_proposal_ready(proposal_id)` for each.
   433	   - **Phase 3 of the write — submit.**
   434	     `store.submit(task_id, token, PlanSubmission(status="success",
   435	     proposal_ids=tuple(proposal_ids)))`.
   436	   - Drop the token from the session.
   437	   - Render `planner_submitted.html`.
   438	
   439	   The narrowest unsafe window — orphaned `ready` proposals not
   440	   yet referenced by a submitted plan task — exists between

