   440	   yet referenced by a submitted plan task — exists between
   441	   Phase 2 and Phase 3. If Phase 3 fails after Phase 2 succeeded
   442	   for at least one proposal, the orchestrator could in principle
   443	   dispatch implement tasks for ready-but-unreferenced proposals.
   444	   We accept this narrow window for the reference impl,
   445	   documented as a known limitation; the spec-level fix
   446	   (atomic ready-and-submit) is out of scope for Phase 9 chunk 1
   447	   and applies equally to the existing scripted planner host.
   448	   The error page on Phase-3 failure surfaces the orphaned
   449	   proposal IDs explicitly so an operator can manually reclaim
   450	   the plan task and let the orchestrator re-dispatch a fresh
   451	   plan attempt.
   452	4. **Submit error** (`POST /planner/{task_id}/submit?status=error`):
   453	   - CSRF check.
   454	   - `store.submit(task_id, token, PlanSubmission(status="error"))`.
   455	   - No proposals are written.
   456	   - Drop the token. Render `planner_submitted.html`.
   457	5. **Phase-3 retry-before-orphan.** Per
   458	   `spec/v0/07-wire-protocol.md` §6 the resubmit semantics are
   459	   defined: a content-equivalent resubmit returns 200, a
   460	   divergent resubmit returns 409
   461	   `eden://error/conflicting-resubmission`. Before declaring
   462	   proposals orphaned, the UI retries the same `submit` call up
   463	   to 3 times with exponential backoff on transport failures,
   464	   and on a clean response treats the submission as committed.
   465	   The orphaned-proposals error page is reached only after the
   466	   retries are exhausted with an indeterminate result, or the
   467	   server returns a definitive error.
   468	6. **Reclaim path on expired/invalid claim token.** If any
   469	   `store.claim` / `store.submit` returns one of the closed
   470	   wire-protocol errors —
   471	   - `eden://error/wrong-token` (presented token != stored
   472	     token; chapter 07 §7),
   473	   - `eden://error/illegal-transition` (state-machine
   474	     violation, e.g. another worker reclaimed after expiry),
   475	   - `eden://error/conflicting-resubmission` (resubmit
   476	     disagreed with committed payload),
   477	   - `eden://error/invalid-precondition` (e.g. trial state
   478	     differs from required) —
   479	   the form re-renders the planner list with a banner naming
   480	   the canonical error type and offering "claim again." Field
   481	   input is preserved across the re-render so the user does not
   482	   lose work-in-progress.
   483	7. **Errors** at any other point: re-render the form with
   484	   field-level messages; do not lose user input.
   485	
   486	`proposal_id` is generated server-side using `uuid.uuid4().hex`, the
   487	same pattern the orchestrator service uses for task IDs.
   488	
   489	### D. Expired-claim sweeper (cross-package, makes TTL operational)
   490	
   491	Setting `expires_at` on every claim is just metadata; recovery requires
   492	something that actually calls `reclaim(task_id, "expired")` on
   493	expired claims. The reference stack has no such sweeper today; this
   494	chunk adds one. Without it, the `--claim-ttl-seconds` flag would be
   495	load-bearing on paper only.
   496	
   497	- New module `eden_dispatch.sweep` exposing
   498	  `sweep_expired_claims(store, *, now) -> int` (returns count
   499	  reclaimed): iterates `store.list_tasks(state="claimed")`, parses
   500	  each `expires_at` (skipping rows where it is `None`), and for
   501	  each one strictly less than `now` calls `store.reclaim(task_id,
   502	  "expired")`. Per-task errors are logged but do not abort the
   503	  sweep — sweeping is best-effort; the next iteration retries.
   504	- `reference/services/orchestrator/src/eden_orchestrator/loop.py`
   505	  calls `sweep_expired_claims(store, now=datetime.now(UTC))` once
   506	  per iteration before `run_orchestrator_iteration`. This couples
   507	  expired-claim recovery to the same poll cadence as the rest of
   508	  the dispatch loop, with no new background thread or wire-level
   509	  notification. Adding the call here (vs. inside
   510	  `run_orchestrator_iteration`) keeps the latter semantically
   511	  pure: it stays the dispatch-and-finalize body, sweeping is a
   512	  separate cross-cutting maintenance pass.
   513	- New test
   514	  `reference/packages/eden-dispatch/tests/test_sweep.py` covering:
   515	  expired claim is reclaimed and emits `task.reclaimed`; non-expired
   516	  claim is left alone; absent `expires_at` is left alone; per-task
   517	  reclaim failure does not abort the sweep.
   518	- The Phase 8b real-subprocess e2e test remains green: it
   519	  doesn't exercise expired claims, but the sweeper is a no-op on
   520	  fresh claims.
   521	
   522	This is the smallest cross-package change that makes the UI's
   523	TTL claim real today, and it's reusable by every future role
   524	that issues claims (implementer / evaluator UI modules in 9c /
   525	9d / 9e).
   526	
   527	### E. Documentation updates
   528	
   529	- `reference/services/web-ui/README.md` — full surface, the auth
   530	  model, how to run locally, the planner flow described above.
   531	- `reference/README.md` — flip the `web-ui` row from "(Phase 9; not
   532	  yet started)" to a current-status entry pointing at this chunk.
   533	- `AGENTS.md` — add a "Phase 9 chunk 1 complete" status block leading
   534	  the existing chain; document the new service in the Commands
   535	  table.
   536	- `docs/roadmap.md` — flip the Phase 9 unit list to "9a + 9b
   537	  complete; 9c–9e pending" with a one-line summary of what shipped;
   538	  call out that the expired-claim sweeper landed alongside as a
   539	  cross-cutting prerequisite.
   540	
   541	### F. CI
   542	
   543	The `python-test`, `python-lint`, and `python-typecheck` jobs already
   544	include the workspace; they pick up the new package with `uv sync`.
   545	No new CI job is needed for this chunk. The `pytest.mark.e2e` test
   546	is gated behind `-m e2e` exactly as the existing one is (so default
   547	runs stay fast); the e2e job in CI runs with `-m e2e`.
   548	
   549	## What does **not** change
   550	
   551	- `spec/v0/**` — no normative changes. The UI is non-normative
   552	  reference material; chapter 07 (wire protocol) is the only
   553	  cross-component contract this UI consumes, and it stays as-is.
   554	- `eden-wire`, `eden-contracts`, `eden-storage`, `eden-git` — no
   555	  API changes. If a need surfaces during implementation, it gets
   556	  called out in the impl-review and either done as a separate
   557	  spec-aware change or deferred.
   558	- `eden-dispatch` — gains a new module
   559	  `eden_dispatch.sweep.sweep_expired_claims` (additive; documented
   560	  in §D). `run_orchestrator_iteration` and the scripted workers
   561	  are not modified.
   562	- All other reference services — their CLIs, behavior, and tests are
   563	  untouched.
   564	
   565	## Verification
   566	
   567	Before declaring the chunk done, all of the following hold:
   568	
