   640	    convergence.
   641	13. PR, CI green, squash-merge.
   642	
   643	## Risks
   644	
   645	- **Stranded human claims.** Mitigated end-to-end: the UI sets
   646	  `expires_at = now + --claim-ttl-seconds` on every claim, and the
   647	  new §D sweeper (`eden_dispatch.sweep.sweep_expired_claims`,
   648	  invoked from the orchestrator service's loop) actually issues
   649	  the `expired` reclaim. Phase 9e adds an explicit
   650	  operator-reclaim button as a faster recovery path. The UI must
   651	  not retry claims server-side for a user who doesn't return —
   652	  that would mask the issue.
   653	- **Partial proposal writes.** The Phase 1 → Phase 2 → Phase 3
   654	  ordering in §C narrows the unsafe window to "ready proposals
   655	  not yet referenced by a submitted plan task." The Phase-3
   656	  retry-before-orphan policy (per §07 §6 idempotent resubmit)
   657	  collapses transport-only failures into successes; only a
   658	  definitive divergent-payload server response or 3 indeterminate
   659	  retries in a row falls through to the operator-recovery error
   660	  page. A spec-level fix (atomic `mark_ready_and_submit`) is out
   661	  of scope for Phase 9 chunk 1; the residual gap applies equally
   662	  to the existing scripted planner host.
   663	- **Experiment-config drift.** The UI loads its own copy of
   664	  `experiment-config.yaml`; if it diverges from the
   665	  task-store-server's copy, planner-side validation could pass on
   666	  inputs the evaluator's metrics_schema would later reject. Phase
   667	  12's control plane is the right fix; for now the start-up
   668	  `experiment_id` mismatch check catches the loud cases.
   669	- **CSRF / cookie attribute regressions.** The cookie/CSRF policy
   670	  is enforced by `tests/test_security_invariants.py`. Any change
   671	  that loosens an attribute or skips the CSRF check breaks the
   672	  test, by design.
   673	- **Bearer-token leak via templating.** Mitigated by the
   674	  bearer-leak unit test, the JSON-line log redaction, and the
   675	  manual `grep -r "$EDEN_SHARED_TOKEN"` verification step. A
   676	  reviewer should still spot-check any new template that
   677	  receives the configuration object.
   678	- **`itsdangerous` session-secret rotation.** Out of scope for this
   679	  chunk; restarting the service with a different `--session-secret`
   680	  invalidates outstanding sessions, which is the documented
   681	  behavior. A real auth phase replaces this anyway.
   682	- **Vendored HTMX bit-rot.** Pin the version in `pyproject.toml`
   683	  comments and check the SHA-256 in `web-ui/README.md`; bumping is a
   684	  one-line follow-up but not silent.
   685	- **HTMX surprises.** If a partial-update interaction turns out to
   686	  need a feature HTMX doesn't cleanly support, fall back to
   687	  full-page submits for that flow rather than reaching for a JS
   688	  framework. The CSS is already a single file; the templates degrade
   689	  gracefully.
   690	- **Test scope creep.** The existing Phase 8b e2e test takes ~3
   691	  seconds because it forks five processes. Adding a second e2e test
   692	  that forks two more (task-store + UI) keeps it on the order of
   693	  another ~3 seconds; this is acceptable. If e2e total exceeds
   694	  ~30 seconds we revisit consolidating, but not preemptively.
   695	- **Reviewers' default expectation of a SPA.** The "Tech stack —
   696	  decision and alternatives considered" section is deliberately
   697	  detailed precisely because reviewers may default to "modern means
   698	  React." The codex-review should specifically scrutinize that
   699	  decision.

